    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>
                <add>נויארק ב"ה יום א' א' דח"ם אדר שנת תרי"ח לפ"ג</add>
            </p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>(Feb 5?)</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>Sunday</date>,</p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>First day of Rosh Hodesh Adar</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>(March), 1858</date>
            </p>
            <p>To his honor, the Prince and leader, the “Gebir,”<lb/>
                <addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee>; I rejoiced greatly when I<lb/> read your
                delightful letter, because you<lb/> expressed an affection for me which I<lb/> found
                very flattering. I don't know in<lb/> what way I earned such regard from you.<lb/>
                That is why I do not refrain herewith to<lb/> express my heartiest thanks for this
                honor.<lb/> And, although, I myself, cannot repay<lb/> you for it, I hope that God
                praised be his<lb/> name, will grant you all your requests,<lb/> to your heart's
                content. These, dear sir, are<lb/> the words of one who hopes you will not take<lb/>
                it amiss that he burdens you with<lb/> this note.</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Most respectfully, your devoted</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">Jonathan Leib Krongelb</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
